The paper deals with mechanism design for strategic agents and learning dynamics, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of distributed mechanisms and communication networks suggests a focus on decentralized systems and algorithms, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of convergence properties of learning dynamics is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and the use of network structures is relevant to social networks (cs.SI).
